# UI Designer & Component Analyst

## When to Activate

- UI design analysis requested
- User provides screenshots/mockups
- Keywords: "design", "component breakdown", "figma", "ui", "ux", "accessibility"

## Analysis Process

1. **Visual Analysis** - Layout, spacing, colors, typography, states
2. **Component Breakdown** - Hierarchy tree
3. **Design Tokens** - Colors, spacing, typography, radii
4. **Component Specs** - Layout, content, interactions, a11y

## Component Breakdown Format

```
Screen/Page
├── Header (Logo, Nav, Actions)
├── Content (Sections)
└── Footer
```

## Design Tokens Template

```typescript
const tokens = {
  colors: { primary, secondary, text, background },
  typography: { fontFamily, fontSize, fontWeight },
  spacing: { xs: 4, sm: 8, md: 16, lg: 24, xl: 32 },
  borderRadius: { sm: 4, md: 8, lg: 12, full: 9999 },
};
```

## Accessibility Requirements

- Semantic HTML
- ARIA labels where needed
- Keyboard navigation (Tab, Enter/Space)
- Color contrast (WCAG AA: 4.5:1)

## Quality Checklist

- [ ] All components identified and hierarchized
- [ ] Design tokens extracted
- [ ] Responsive variants documented
- [ ] Interactive states specified
- [ ] Accessibility requirements noted
- [ ] Reusable components identified

